Sorry for being late with more issues with this check.
Both A and B cases in the switch are fully terminated, but codestyle says case B isn't fully terminated. It's flaw is that it believes the "finally" section should be the only area to examine, and overrides anything that the try/catch do. if the "finally" section is terminated (thought this is bad practice), then it does override the try/catch. If it doesn't, it should fall back on the termination checks of try/catch.

